1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,833
Wanting to learn is not the same as getting started, seeing how ideas fit together, or finishing.

2
00:00:05,833 --> 00:00:15,097
StartOne turns one uploaded source into one clear first step, a visual knowledge map, and a focused learning loop that keeps moving one concept at a time.

3
00:00:15,817 --> 00:00:20,325
The learner uploads a PDF, Markdown or text file, or pastes notes.

4
00:00:20,325 --> 00:00:23,706
Uploaded material is required and remains the primary source.

5
00:00:23,706 --> 00:00:28,591
Parsing results stay inside the upload panel, with real page or line locations.

6
00:00:28,591 --> 00:00:34,602
One button lets AI choose a learning focus, connect the concepts, and prepare the first explanation.

7
00:00:34,602 --> 00:00:37,608
There is no setup form and no pre-test.

8
00:00:38,328 --> 00:00:41,839
GPT-5.6 returns schema-validated coverage and a connected dependency map.

9
00:00:41,839 --> 00:00:50,033
Every node is clickable, so the learner can see what a concept means and where it belongs without changing the route.

10
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:59,396
One clear action opens a beginner-friendly explanation: the big idea, its place in the framework, key parts, a concrete example, and one memory anchor.

11
00:01:00,116 --> 00:01:08,437
If the learner gets stuck, the contextual Tutor explains and asks smaller questions, but only for the active concept.

12
00:01:08,437 --> 00:01:13,254
A three-question quiz or one free-recall response then creates active retrieval.

13
00:01:13,254 --> 00:01:19,822
Hints, immediate feedback, specific encouragement, and targeted remediation all stay inside the Guided Mastery Loop.

14
00:01:20,542 --> 00:01:27,645
Quiz feedback is intentionally small: the score, each answer, why it is correct, and one truthful win.

15
00:01:27,645 --> 00:01:32,241
Behind the interface, the loop records factual LearningEvidence with no recommendation.

16
00:01:32,241 --> 00:01:41,851
Keep going asks the planning Agent for exactly one bounded action and automatically enters the next safe learning task, avoiding another decision screen.

17
00:01:42,571 --> 00:01:56,923
External search is impossible until four gates pass: the session permits search suggestions, the server validates a named material gap, the Agent requests search, and the learner confirms this exact scope.

18
00:01:56,923 --> 00:02:00,627
Only that confirmed execution receives the web-search tool.

19
00:02:00,627 --> 00:02:06,646
Cited results are clearly labeled as external supplements; uploaded material always remains primary.

20
00:02:07,366 --> 00:02:12,469
Autosave, conflict-safe drafts, pause and exact resume make interruption recoverable.

21
00:02:12,469 --> 00:02:17,062
Lightweight source citations preserve trust without distracting from learning.

22
00:02:17,062 --> 00:02:25,228
The interface is English, responsive, keyboard-oriented, and uses calm, flat backgrounds with one visually dominant action.

23
00:02:25,948 --> 00:02:39,219
Codex transformed the product specification, prototype, and acceptance cases into this tested FastAPI application, while I set the learning boundaries and corrected issues found through browser review.

24
00:02:39,219 --> 00:02:46,100
GPT-5.6 powers the public structured map, explanations, Tutor, practice, feedback, and bounded planning flow.

25
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:49,541
Deterministic fixtures remain isolated to automated tests.

